    steps: [
      { stepNumber: 1, title: 'Pressure cook the lentils', instruction: 'Drain soaked urad dal and rajma. Add to pressure cooker with 600ml fresh water and a pinch of salt. Cook on high for 8-10 whistles — both urad and rajma must be completely broken down and tender. Natural pressure release. The urad should be releasing starch into the water, making it slightly viscous. Mash lightly with a whisk.', durationMins: 30, technique: 'pressure_cook', kitchenNote: 'This step is done the previous evening at cloud kitchen scale. Cook overnight at low heat after pressure cooking for best depth of flavour — the original dum method.' },
      { stepNumber: 2, title: 'Build the tomato base', instruction: 'Heat ghee and oil in a heavy pot. Add finely chopped onion and cook 8 minutes until deeply golden. Add ginger-garlic paste and cook 3 minutes. Add blended tomato puree and cook 8-10 minutes on medium-high heat until the oil separates and the tomato is dark red. Add red chilli powder, coriander powder, and turmeric. Cook 2 more minutes.', durationMins: 22, technique: 'saute', kitchenNote: 'The tomato must be cooked until completely dried out and dark — this is what gives dal makhani its characteristic deep red colour and round flavour.' },
      { stepNumber: 3, title: 'Combine and simmer', instruction: 'Add pressure-cooked lentils to the tomato base. Stir well — the dal will look lighter at first but will deepen as it simmers. Add 100ml water if needed for consistency. Simmer uncovered on low heat 15 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes, until the dal is very thick and the masala is fully integrated. The dal should coat the back of a spoon thickly. Add garam masala, crushed kasuri methi, and a finishing drizzle of 4g ghee. Do not stir the ghee in — let it pool on top.', durationMins: 18, technique: 'simmer', kitchenNote: 'Dal makhani improves for 24 hours after cooking — batches cooked the previous day are superior to same-day preparation. Reheat gently with a splash of water.' },
      { stepNumber: 4, title: 'Make raita and pack', instruction: 'Whisk curd smooth. Mix in grated cucumber, lemon juice, roasted crushed cumin, and a pinch of salt. Pack dal in main compartment with ghee on top. Brown rice in side compartment. Raita in sealed 60ml pot. Garnish with fresh coriander.', durationMins: 4, technique: 'assemble', kitchenNote: 'Do not pre-mix the ghee into the dal during packing — the visual of golden ghee pooling on top of dark dal is part of the experience.' },
    ],
